text: Botoşani (pronunciation in Romanian: is the capital city of Botoşani County, in the northern part of Moldavia, Romania. It has a population of 115,609 people as of the year 2002 Today, it is best known as the birthplace of many celebrated Romanians, including Mihai Eminescu and Nicolae Iorga. == Sport == Football is represented in Botoşani by the team FC Botoşani. == References == Category:County capitals of Romania Category:Municipalities of Romania Category:Cities in Romania Category:Botoșani County
title: Botoșani
